<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="freeze-v">freeze <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /friːz/    美 /friːz/  </p>
<p>(froze, frozen)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 结冰：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The lake was <strong>frozen over</strong>. 
湖面封冻。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Fresh water freezes at 0°C. 
淡水在摄氏零度结冰。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(人) 冻僵；(水管、机器等) 冻住：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Two men were <strong>frozen to death</strong> on the mountain.
有两个男子在山上冻死了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Our water pipes <strong>froze</strong> ( <strong>up</strong> ) last winter.
去年冬天,我们的水管子冻住了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(天气) 冰冷：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It</strong> may <strong>freeze</strong> tonight, so bring those plants inside.
今晚大概很冷，所以把植物都搬进来。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>冷冻；冷藏：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Tomatoes don't freeze well.
番茄不宜冷冻。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'll buy extra meat and just freeze it.
我要多买些肉冷冻起来。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>停住不动</strong></h4>
<p>to stop moving suddenly：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Freeze, or I'll shoot!
不许动，否则我开枪了！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The smile froze on his face.
笑容在他脸上僵住了。</p><footer>2013 湖北</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>frozen /'frəʊzn/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You must be frozen! Come and sit by the fire.
你肯定冻僵了！快坐到炉火边上来。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Americans always drive to supermarkets to buy canned and frozen foods for the week.
美国人总是开车去超市买一个星期所需的罐头食品和冷冻食品。</p><footer>2014 陕西改</footer></div></div>